rComments: Any of Professor Watson's Digital Humanities courses are extremely rewarding. Her subject matter is always engaging, and she goes out of her way to make the material accessible and clear. Also, she is always available to lend a hand when needed and provides very thorough feedback on assignments. I would recommend any class with her.

rComments: I took a Digital Humanities class with Prof. Watson and it was great. I believe it was the first time the course was run, but you wouldn't be able to tell by the curriculum, which was super clear and included genuinely engaging material. I'd 100% recommend the course and prof! She's very sweet and passionate about her field.

Everything she taught was clear and intentional. She was warm and inviting and very obviously cared about the subject material. I would have liked to see more explanations of how the projects related to the subject, however.

rComments: Jada Watson is my by far my favourite professor. She is better than any of my high school teacher and makes you definitely feel like she cares about your future. She is extremely intelligent and definitely a true role model! I aspire to be more like her.
